{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id52c86a33-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1962"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1962"},"text":"§ 1962.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Lien","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Every judgment rendered by a district court within a State shall be a lien on the property located in such State in the same manner, to the same extent and under the same conditions as a judgment of a court of general jurisdiction in such State, and shall cease to be a lien in the same manner and time. This section does not apply to judgments entered in favor of the United States. Whenever the law of any State requires a judgment of a State court to be registered, recorded, docketed or indexed, or any other act to be done, in a particular manner, or in a certain office or county or parish before such lien attaches, such requirements shall apply only if the law of such State authorizes the judgment of a court of the United States to be registered, recorded, docketed, indexed or otherwise conformed to rules and requirements relating to judgments of the courts of the State.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id52c86a34-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646"},"text":"June 25, 1948, ch. 646","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/958"},"text":"62 Stat. 958","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/647/tXXXVI/s3627"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–647, title XXXVI, § 3627","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/4965"},"text":"104 Stat. 4965","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id52c86a35-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id52c86a36-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., §§ 812 and 814 (R.S. § 967; ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1888-08-01/ch729/s1"},"text":"Aug. 1, 1888, ch. 729, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/25/357"},"text":"25 Stat. 357","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s291"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 291","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/36/1167"},"text":"36 Stat. 1167","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1912-08-17/ch300"},"text":"Aug. 17, 1912, ch. 300","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/37/311"},"text":"37 Stat. 311","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section consolidates sections 812 and 814 of title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., with changes in phraseology necessary to effect consolidation and to clarify the meaning of such sections.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Omitted words “or decree” after “judgments” as unnecessary inasmuch as Rule 54(a) of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure by definition of judgment includes a decree.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Words “in the State of Louisiana” after “or parish” were omitted as unnecessary.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A reference to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s813"},"text":"section 813 of title 28","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C., 1940 ed., was omitted, since such section is omitted from this revision as covered by Rule 79(c) of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id52c86a37-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id52c86a38-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1990—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/647"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–647","children":[],"tail":" inserted after first sentence “This section does not apply to judgments entered in favor of the United States.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id52c86a39-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id52c86a3a-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1990 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/647"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–647","children":[],"tail":" effective 180 days after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1990","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/647/s3631"},"text":"section 3631 of Pub. L. 101–647","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s3001"},"text":"section 3001 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
